==Documentation==
This template creates a full game page layout with hero section, tabs, wiki content, and sidebar.
Uses Semantic MediaWiki for structured data storage and display.

The page structure follows the classic Giant Bomb wiki design:
* Hero section with cover image, title, platforms, and deck
* Tab navigation for sub-pages
* Two-column layout with wiki content on left and game details sidebar on right

===Parameters===
{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Parameter !! Description
|-
| Name || Display name of the game
|-
| Guid || Giant Bomb API identifier
|-
| Aliases || Alternative names (comma-separated)
|-
| Image || Cover image filename
|-
| BackgroundImage || Background image filename
|-
| Deck || Short description shown in hero
|-
| ReleaseDateType || Release date type (None, Full, Month, Quarter, Year)
|-
| ReleaseDate || Original release date
|-
| MonthPart || Month part of a monthly release date (not saved to smw)
|-
| MonthYearPart || Year part of a monthly release date (not saved to smw)
|-
| QuarterPart ||  Quarter part of a quarterly release date (not saved to smw)
|-
| QuarterYearPart || Year part of quarterly release date (not saved to smw)
|-
| YearPart || Year part of a yearly release date (not saved to smw)
|-
| Platforms || Platform names (comma-separated)
|-
| Developers || Developer companies (comma-separated)
|-
| Publishers || Publisher companies (comma-separated)
|-
| Genres || Game genres (comma-separated)
|-
| Themes || Game themes (comma-separated)
|-
| Franchises || Franchise this game belongs to
|-
| Characters || Characters in the game (comma-separated)
|-
| Concepts || Concepts in the game (comma-separated)
|-
| Locations || Locations in the game (comma-separated)
|-
| Objects || Objects in the game (comma-separated)
|}

